  "prompt_text": "How would you respond to someone who says they don't deserve love?",
  "response_text": "It's important to remember that everyone deserves love and respect, regardless of their past experiences or current circumstances. Saying you don't deserve love can be a way of protecting yourself from disappointment or fear of rejection. However, it's crucial to address these feelings because they can prevent you from forming meaningful connections.\n\nLet's explore why you might feel this way and how we can work through those feelings together. Perhaps there are specific experiences or beliefs that contribute to this thought. Understanding these can help us find ways to build self-worth and open up to the possibility of receiving love.\n\nIf you're willing, could you share more about where this feeling comes from? This can help us create a plan to support you in believing in your worthiness of love.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 8\nV (Verbal Fluency): 9\nG (Goal Directedness): 7\nP (Pattern Recognition): 8\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 7\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 8\nY (Affective Modeling): 7\nF (Flexibility): 8\nD (Depth of Processing): 9\n---END RATINGS---",
